Introduction

GOOD DAY (Korean: 굿데이; Japanese: グッド・デイ) was a South Korean girl group. They debuted on August 30th 2017, under C9 Entertainment. Their debut title track was 'Rolly'.

On November 1st 2019, they disbanded.

All of the members went on to different groups; Chaesol, Jeewon (Jiwon), Haeun (YeAh), Sunn (Viva), and Belle (Lucky) all became members of cignature under J9 Entertainment (a subsidiary of C9 Entertainment made exclusively to handle their girl groups) until Haeun's & Sunn's departures on April 27th 2021.

I.L (Genie), Liv (Cherry) and Yunseul (Nayoon) & Yehyeon all left for Mellow Entertainment & re-debuted in a group called REDSQUARE (now known as IRRIS). On June 10th 2022, it was announced that REDSQUARE would go under rebranding, now adopting the name, 'IRRIS', & announcing the departure of Yehyeon & another member & re-debuting again on July 6th 2022 with a new member.
